In English, it is ‘an administrative region in the Federal District OF Brazil’ (in this case, ‘it is ‘of’, not ‘in). People should study grammar and orthography before attempting any edit on any page of this website. Even if those errors are unintentional, this is considered to be vandalism, and the person doing it will be banned and blocked.

In English, it is ‘an administrative region in the Federal District OF Brazil’ (in this case, ‘it is ‘of’, not ‘in). People should study grammar and orthography before attempting any edit on any page of this website. Even if those errors are unintentional, this is considered to be vandalism, and the person doing it will be banned and blocked.

There isn’t ‘Região Administrativa de Brasília’ (Administrative Region of Brasilia’), the correct is ‘Região Administrativa do Plano Piloto’ (‘Administrative Region of Plano Piloto’). Furthermore, in Portuguese, in this case the correct is ‘do’ (Plano Piloto), not ‘de’.

In Portuguese, it is ‘Região Administrativa DO Gama’ (in this case, it is ‘do’, not ‘de’). In English, it is ‘an administrative region in the Federal District OF Brazil’ (in this case, ‘it is ‘of’, not ‘in). People should study grammar and orthography — both in Portuguese and English — before attempting any edit on any page of this website. Even if those errors are unintentional, this is considered to be vandalism, and the person doing it will be banned and block.

Undid the edits by Specdens and added a reference. Again, the user Specdens (with a history of randomly deleting content from articles and vandalism) deleted some parts of the text and made if full of errors. Example: “The administrative region's name comes FROM TO Brasília's Botanical Garden”? The user is just deleting the parts he doesn’t like and the article stays a mess of words.

Undid the edits by the user Specdens.  What is the sense of “it is basically a gated communities and private estates”? “It is basically A gated communities (…)”? “The administrative region's name comes FROM TO Brasília's Botanical Garden”? The user is just deleting the parts he doesn’t like and the article stays a mess of words. Although the user deleted everything on his Talk Page, he has a long history of deleting content of Wikipedia without a proper explaining and also vandalism.

Undid the previous edits from the anonymous user. The correct is ‘Região Administrativa do Jardim Botânico’ (check the official government website: https://www.admjardimbotanico.df.gov.br). The anonymous user also deleted the word ‘suburban’; although it is very common among illiterate Brazilians, the word ‘suburb’ is NOT a synonymous of ‘favela’ or ‘shantytown’; there are suburbs of all social classes (that’s why I also added the term ‘middle and upper class’ in the article).
